If there's a more clear case
of eminent domain, I've never seen it.

717
00:54:50,597 --> 00:54:53,182
I'm going to recommend
we militarize this project.

718
00:54:53,351 --> 00:54:55,726
What? This is my project.

719
00:54:55,894 --> 00:54:59,271
Nobody knows more about these scenarios
than I do. David, tell them...

720
00:54:59,440 --> 00:55:02,817
Excuse me, could we calm down here?

721
00:55:03,027 --> 00:55:07,697
Now, I'm going to recommend that
Dr. Drumlin coordinate the decryption effort.

722
00:55:07,864 --> 00:55:11,242
However, in light of Dr. Arroway's
long experience in these matters...

723
00:55:11,409 --> 00:55:15,621
...for the time being, she will continue
to direct operations at the VLA...

724
00:55:15,789 --> 00:55:20,460
...understanding that future discoveries
will be kept in strictest confidence...

725
00:55:20,628 --> 00:55:22,545
...until such time as the president...

726
00:55:22,713 --> 00:55:26,715
...can decide the most suitable
course of action. Understood?

727
00:55:26,884 --> 00:55:28,092
Yes.

728
00:55:28,385 --> 00:55:31,012
MAN:
This is CNN Breaking News.

729
00:55:31,179 --> 00:55:34,139
The president made a statement,
calling the message from Vega...

730
00:55:34,349 --> 00:55:36,476
...one of the most stunning insights
into our...

731
00:55:36,684 --> 00:55:41,688
Attendance at religious services has
risen a dramatic 39 percent in recent days.

732
00:55:41,856 --> 00:55:45,692
...as police in three German divisions
clashed with neo-Nazi protesters.

733
00:55:45,860 --> 00:55:47,985
So it turns out
there's life on other planets.

734
00:55:48,195 --> 00:55:51,824
Boy, this is really gonna change
the Miss Universe contest.

735
00:55:52,492 --> 00:55:56,829
Health officials from around the world are
concerned that the message from Vega...

736
00:55:56,996 --> 00:55:59,623
...might trigger a rash of mass suicides...

737
00:55:59,833 --> 00:56:02,458
...not unlike the recent cult deaths
near San Diego...

738
00:56:02,668 --> 00:56:04,628
Even a scientist has to admit...

739
00:56:04,838 --> 00:56:09,340
...that there are some pretty serious
religious overtones to all this.

740
00:56:09,509 --> 00:56:11,677
Let's hear from someone
whose organization...

741
00:56:11,885 --> 00:56:14,429
...has been accused of conducting
its own inquisition:

742
00:56:14,597 --> 00:56:17,224
Richard Rank,
head of the Conservative coalition.

743
00:56:17,391 --> 00:56:18,474
Thank you.

744
00:56:18,643 --> 00:56:23,021
This is yet another example of science
intruding into matters of faith.

745
00:56:24,065 --> 00:56:27,358
This means they
have been reacting to TV signals...

746
00:56:27,568 --> 00:56:30,487
...they got from the 1930s.
They're just getting them.

747
00:56:30,697 --> 00:56:34,365
Imagine how disappointed
they're gonna be if they're Cubs fans.

748
00:56:34,534 --> 00:56:37,702
We now take you to Jeremy Roth,
who is reporting on events...

749
00:56:37,911 --> 00:56:41,373
...at the Very Large Array
near Socorro, New Mexico.

750
00:56:41,583 --> 00:56:43,416
Like a bolt from the blue it came.

751
00:56:43,585 --> 00:56:47,753
The message from Vega has caused
thousands of believers and non-believers...

752
00:56:47,922 --> 00:56:51,842
...to descend upon the VLA facility
here in the desert of New Mexico.

753
00:56:52,050 --> 00:56:54,552
Many have come to protest,
many to pray...

754
00:56:54,721 --> 00:56:59,557
...but most have come to participate
in what has become the best show in town.

755
00:57:06,190 --> 00:57:09,317
[CHATTERING]

756
00:57:26,418 --> 00:57:28,335
[CHANTING]

757
00:57:59,576 --> 00:58:05,456
That's right. I'll be there in Vega,
thank you very much.

758
00:58:08,460 --> 00:58:11,378
CHORUS [SINGING]: Hajl to Vega
Hail to Vega, Hail to Vega

759
00:58:11,547 --> 00:58:14,798
Hail to Vega

760
00:58:16,134 --> 00:58:17,802
But they have failed!

761
00:58:18,387 --> 00:58:20,929
It's the same people who,
again and again...

762
00:58:21,097 --> 00:58:23,516
...have brought us
to the brink of destruction.

763
00:58:23,724 --> 00:58:27,769
Who've polluted our air,
who've poisoned our water.

764
00:58:28,981 --> 00:58:30,981
Now these scientists...

765
00:58:31,983 --> 00:58:33,817
...have had their chance.

766
00:58:33,985 --> 00:58:37,403
Are these the kind of people...

767
00:58:37,572 --> 00:58:40,699
...that you want
talking to your God for you?

768
00:58:40,865 --> 00:58:42,826
[PEOPLE YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

769
00:58:45,161 --> 00:58:47,246
MAN [ON TV]:
Efforts continue around the clock.

770
00:58:47,581 --> 00:58:51,166
But for now, almost 2 full weeks
after the message's arrival...

771
00:58:51,335 --> 00:58:54,503
...scientists here at the VLA
still have no answers...

772
00:58:54,672 --> 00:58:56,422
...only more questions.

773
00:58:56,590 --> 00:59:00,302
Jeremy Roth, CNN,
Soccorro, New Mexico.

774
00:59:00,469 --> 00:59:03,804
More on the quest
for the message's meaning, after this.

775
00:59:06,641 --> 00:59:08,393
They gotta line up somehow.

776
00:59:08,561 --> 00:59:10,519
Yeah, well, this one doesn't fit, either.

777
00:59:10,688 --> 00:59:13,356
We've tried over a million permutations.

778
00:59:13,523 --> 00:59:17,027
Always, I can only get
three corners to fit.

779
00:59:18,028 --> 00:59:20,155
I don't understand their significance.

780
01:00:02,030 --> 01:00:04,739
What...? Somebody broke in...

781
01:00:06,742 --> 01:00:08,786
[PHONE RINGS]

782
01:00:11,081 --> 01:00:12,246
Hello?

783
01:00:13,166 --> 01:00:16,585
Hey, listen, I don't know who you are,
but you broke into the database...

784
01:00:19,422 --> 01:00:21,130
What? Now?

785
01:00:23,592 --> 01:00:24,760
Where?

786
01:00:24,927 --> 01:00:26,844
[FAX MACHINE HUMMING]

787
01:00:37,773 --> 01:00:39,190
I'll be there.

788
01:01:06,802 --> 01:01:08,137
MAN 1:
You should feel fortunate.

789
01:01:08,887 --> 01:01:10,389
He hardly lands for anyone.

790
01:01:41,961 --> 01:01:43,920
MAN 2:
Dr. Arroway...

791
01:01:47,842 --> 01:01:49,177
...I presume?

792
01:01:50,471 --> 01:01:51,596
Mr. Hadden.

793
01:01:52,889 --> 01:01:56,141
I've had my eye on you
a long time, doctor.

794
01:01:56,934 --> 01:02:00,438
I consider you one of my
most valuable long-term investments.

795
01:02:02,315 --> 01:02:04,692
And when it comes to my investments...

796
01:02:06,487 --> 01:02:09,155
...I always do my homework.

797
01:02:13,869 --> 01:02:15,619
Eleanor Ann Arroway...

798
01:02:15,829 --> 01:02:18,331
...born 25th August, 1964...

799
01:02:18,539 --> 01:02:20,123
...De Pere, Wisconsin.

800
01:02:20,333 --> 01:02:24,545
Mother, Joanna, died
from complications during childbirth.

801
01:02:25,255 --> 01:02:27,965
Early testing indicated
high predisposition...

802
01:02:28,132 --> 01:02:31,219
...towards science and mathematics.

803
01:02:31,887 --> 01:02:33,054
Father, Theodore...

804
01:02:33,222 --> 01:02:36,766
...advised to provide
enrichment activities along these lines...

805
01:02:36,974 --> 01:02:39,726
...did so conscientiously
until his death...

806
01:02:39,894 --> 01:02:44,563
...from myocardial infarction,
November 10, 1974.

807
01:02:45,148 --> 01:02:48,400
You graduated from
high school in 1979...

808
01:02:48,568 --> 01:02:50,695
...almost two full years early.

809
01:02:52,114 --> 01:02:56,492
Awarded full scholarship, M.I. T,
graduated magna cum laude.

810
01:02:57,452 --> 01:02:59,161
Doctoral work, Cal Tech...

811
01:02:59,371 --> 01:03:02,706
...where you did breakthrough work
on the lanthanide-doped ruby maser...

812
01:03:02,875 --> 01:03:07,003
...dramatically increasing
the sensitivity of radio telescopes.

813
01:03:07,338 --> 01:03:11,048
Subsequently offered a teaching position
at Harvard University...

814
01:03:11,259 --> 01:03:14,344
...which you turned down
to pursue SETI work...

815
01:03:14,554 --> 01:03:17,972
...at the Arecibo Observatory
in Puerto Rico.

816
01:03:20,393 --> 01:03:26,648
Changes in NSF policy
gave rise to certain funding problems...

817
01:03:27,733 --> 01:03:31,735
...at which point
you came to my attention.

818
01:03:33,072 --> 01:03:35,282
You compromised our security codes.

819
01:03:37,742 --> 01:03:39,577
Once upon a time...

820
01:03:41,581 --> 01:03:43,831
...I was a hell of an engineer.

821
01:03:44,000 --> 01:03:46,418
Please, sit, doctor.

822
01:03:46,585 --> 01:03:51,715
I have guests so rarely, it's important to me
that they feel welcome in my home.

823
01:03:52,300 --> 01:03:54,050
You live here?

824
01:03:55,260 --> 01:03:58,597
I find it convenient
to keep my interests...

825
01:03:59,764 --> 01:04:00,891
...mobile.

826
01:04:03,476 --> 01:04:08,396
Anyway, I've had my fill
of life on the ground.

827
01:04:08,898 --> 01:04:11,025
Well, I... I guess I should...

828
01:04:11,483 --> 01:04:15,278
Well, I guess I should thank you
for having bailed me out all that time.

829
01:04:20,619 --> 01:04:22,744
I know a good bet when I see one.

830
01:04:25,123 --> 01:04:28,333
Earl Grey. No sugar, no milk, I believe.

831
01:04:31,295 --> 01:04:33,130
What am I doing here?

832
01:04:34,132 --> 01:04:36,507
[CHUCKLES]

833
01:04:43,474 --> 01:04:46,601
The powers that be
have been very busy lately...

834
01:04:47,436 --> 01:04:52,775
...falling over each other to position
themselves for the game of the millennium.

835
01:04:59,032 --> 01:05:01,824
Maybe I can help deal you back in.

836
01:05:03,077 --> 01:05:05,496
I didn't realize that I was out.

837
01:05:05,996 --> 01:05:08,289
No, maybe not out...

838
01:05:09,000 --> 01:05:11,293
...but certainly being handed your hat.

839
01:05:16,715 --> 01:05:20,385
I've had a long time
to make enemies, doctor.

840
01:05:23,974 --> 01:05:27,809
And there are many governments,
business interests...

841
01:05:27,978 --> 01:05:31,980
...even religious leaders that
would like to see me depart this earth.

842
01:05:33,440 --> 01:05:35,983
And I'll grant them their wish
soon enough.

843
01:05:36,527 --> 01:05:40,070
But before I do,
I wish to make a small contribution.

844
01:05:40,822 --> 01:05:45,409
A final gesture of goodwill to the
people of this little planet that have given...

845
01:05:48,204 --> 01:05:50,998
From whom I have taken so much.

846
01:05:54,460 --> 01:05:55,920
You found the primer.

847
01:05:58,340 --> 01:06:00,215
Clever girl.

848
01:06:00,384 --> 01:06:01,425
Lights.

849
01:06:10,018 --> 01:06:13,186
Pages and pages of data.

850
01:06:13,355 --> 01:06:16,481
Over 63,000 in all.

851
01:06:16,650 --> 01:06:18,735
And on the perimeter of each...

852
01:06:18,902 --> 01:06:22,530
Alignment symbols, a registration mark,
but they don't line up.

853
01:06:23,114 --> 01:06:26,284
They do, if you think like a Vegan.

854
01:06:27,202 --> 01:06:30,204
An alien intelligence
has got be more advanced...

855
01:06:30,371 --> 01:06:34,458
...and that means efficiency
functioning on multiple levels...

856
01:06:34,626 --> 01:06:38,463
...and in multiple dimensions.

857
01:06:42,425 --> 01:06:44,844
Yes, of course!

858
01:06:45,012 --> 01:06:46,054
Where's the primer?

859
01:06:46,554 --> 01:06:47,972
You'll see.

860
01:06:48,474 --> 01:06:52,934
Every three-dimensional page
contains a piece of the primer.

861
01:06:55,103 --> 01:06:58,606
There it was all the time,
staring you in the face.

862
01:06:59,692 --> 01:07:03,612
Buried within the message itself
is the key to decoding it.

863
01:07:03,780 --> 01:07:07,032
Within the layering of the matrix,
we have these basic equations:

864
01:07:08,992 --> 01:07:13,038
So with this very elementary foundation,
they have given us a kind of...

865
01:07:13,206 --> 01:07:15,791
...general scientific vocabulary.

866
01:07:16,000 --> 01:07:18,293
We now have the symbols
for true and false...

867
01:07:18,503 --> 01:07:19,795
This was the key...

868
01:07:19,961 --> 01:07:22,463
...that allowed us
to decipher their language...

869
01:07:22,672 --> 01:07:26,342
...for physics, geometry, chemistry.
Next frame, Ellie.

870
01:07:27,552 --> 01:07:31,514
Yes, and when we apply this
to the rest of the message...

871
01:07:32,266 --> 01:07:33,349
...we find this.

872
01:07:37,938 --> 01:07:40,856
Those look like engineering schematics,
almost like blueprints.

873
01:07:41,025 --> 01:07:42,650
Yeah.

874
01:07:42,818 --> 01:07:43,902
Yes.

875
01:07:44,070 --> 01:07:47,364
It is our belief that
the message contains instructions...

876
01:07:47,572 --> 01:07:51,034
...for building something,
some kind of machine.

877
01:07:51,202 --> 01:07:54,329
A machine? That does what, doctor?

878
01:07:54,496 --> 01:07:56,706
We don't know.
It might be some type...

879
01:07:57,666 --> 01:08:03,213
...of advanced communication device,
or a teaching machine of some kind.

880
01:08:03,713 --> 01:08:07,007
Or it might turn out to be
some kind of a transport.

881
01:08:07,425 --> 01:08:09,885
- Transport?
- There's no proof of that.

882
01:08:10,054 --> 01:08:13,889
The fact is, you don't know what it does.
It could be anything.

883
01:08:14,057 --> 01:08:17,393
Could be a Trojan horse. We build it
and out pours the entire Vegan army.

884
01:08:17,560 --> 01:08:20,229
Why bother risking the personnel?
It could be a weapon.

885
01:08:20,438 --> 01:08:22,730
Right. Some kind of
a doomsday machine.

886
01:08:22,899 --> 01:08:25,400
Exactly. Every time they detect
a new civilization...

887
01:08:25,569 --> 01:08:28,028
...they fax these construction documents
from space.

888
01:08:28,195 --> 01:08:31,823
We poor saps build whatever this is
and blow ourselves to kingdom come.

889
01:08:31,992 --> 01:08:34,909
There's no reason to believe
that their intentions are hostile.

890
01:08:35,078 --> 01:08:39,414
Why is the default position of the egghead
set that aliens would always be benign?

891
01:08:39,582 --> 01:08:42,042
- Why is that, doctor?
- We pose no threat to them.

892
01:08:42,210 --> 01:08:46,630
It would be like us going out of our way
to destroy microbes on an anthill in Africa

893
01:08:46,797 --> 01:08:48,381
DRUMLIN:
That's an interesting analogy.

894
01:08:48,800 --> 01:08:52,970
And how guilty would we feel if we
destroyed a few microbes on an anthill?

895
01:08:53,137 --> 01:08:55,514
I hope you're right, doctor. I really do.

896
01:08:55,681 --> 01:08:59,143
But right now my job is to protect
American lives from any threat.

897
01:08:59,310 --> 01:09:01,645
In that regard, I am obligated
to assume the worst.

898
01:09:01,896 --> 01:09:03,980
Well, yes, and I am forced
to agree with you.

899
01:09:04,149 --> 01:09:05,565
My problem is this:

900
01:09:06,193 --> 01:09:09,403
The content of that message
is morally ambiguous at best.

901
01:09:10,070 --> 01:09:13,615
Now, our internal numbers show
support for this is incredibly soft.

902
01:09:13,783 --> 01:09:16,452
If the president wishes
to stay this course...

903
01:09:16,619 --> 01:09:19,287
...you're gonna find his numbers
going south like a duck.

904
01:09:19,456 --> 01:09:21,873
- This is nuts.
RANK: Excuse me...

905
01:09:22,042 --> 01:09:23,458
...miss.

906
01:09:23,627 --> 01:09:26,002
We know nothing
of these creatures' values.

907
01:09:26,171 --> 01:09:28,963
The fact is, we don't even know
whether they believe in God.

908
01:09:29,131 --> 01:09:32,885
- This doesn't make any sense. If you...
CONSTANTINE: Excuse me, Dr. Arroway.

909
01:09:33,094 --> 01:09:35,554
We won't be suppressing
any opinions here today.

910
01:09:36,430 --> 01:09:39,140
No, of course not. I understand.

911
01:09:39,559 --> 01:09:41,475
What I meant to say...

912
01:09:41,644 --> 01:09:45,104
...is the message was written
in the language of science.

913
01:09:45,271 --> 01:09:48,649
Now, if it had been religious in nature,
it should have taken the form...

914
01:09:48,817 --> 01:09:51,444
...of a burning bush
or a booming voice from the sky.

915
01:09:51,654 --> 01:09:53,738
But a voice from the sky...

916
01:09:54,823 --> 01:09:57,658
...is exactly what you found,
Doctor Arroway.

917
01:10:01,037 --> 01:10:02,997
I'm sorry I'm late, ma'am.

918
01:10:03,164 --> 01:10:08,377
Now, I agree with Mr. Rank
that there are unavoidable...

919
01:10:08,587 --> 01:10:10,755
...religious implications at stake here.

920
01:10:10,922 --> 01:10:13,341
But that doesn't justify
taking an alarmist position.

921
01:10:15,386 --> 01:10:18,136
My hope here is that we can find
a common ground...

922
01:10:18,305 --> 01:10:21,015
...break through any obstacles
that may have kept us apart.

923
01:10:21,182 --> 01:10:24,601
KITZ: Well, perhaps...
- Listen, I need to make one thing very clear.

924
01:10:24,811 --> 01:10:29,439
Our organization will not be placated
with flowery New Age rhetoric...

925
01:10:30,442 --> 01:10:31,943
Mr. President.

926
01:10:33,404 --> 01:10:35,697
The President met
with his top advisors today...

927
01:10:35,863 --> 01:10:39,283
...regarding the latest efforts
to decode the message.

928
01:10:39,451 --> 01:10:44,122
While there has been some progress,
the official line remains a cautious one.

929
01:10:44,289 --> 01:10:48,917
If you're asking when we'll find out
what the purpose of that machine is...

930
01:10:49,920 --> 01:10:52,630
...maybe tomorrow,
maybe next year, maybe never.

931
01:10:57,051 --> 01:11:01,639
There he is. The man with his finger
on the spiritual pulse of the nation.

932
01:11:03,016 --> 01:11:06,435
- It's so good to see you, Ellie.
- You too.

933
01:11:07,686 --> 01:11:11,648
Your discovery, all of this.
It must be a real vindication.

934
01:11:12,317 --> 01:11:13,984
I'm really happy for you.

935
01:11:14,609 --> 01:11:18,572
- Are you?
- Mr. Joss, the president is waiting.

936
01:11:19,948 --> 01:11:23,076
- Okay. Yeah.
- The president is waiting.

937
01:11:26,997 --> 01:11:30,876
- Ellie, see you at the reception tonight?
- Yeah, I wouldn't miss it.

938
01:11:31,043 --> 01:11:32,918
All right, great.

939
01:11:42,930 --> 01:11:45,265
Excuse me, Miss Constantine,
may I speak to you?

940
01:11:45,432 --> 01:11:46,850
Certainly.

941
01:11:48,603 --> 01:11:50,811
- I have a big problem.
- Yes?

942
01:11:50,979 --> 01:11:52,480
Um...

943
01:11:52,648 --> 01:11:55,442
Do you know where I can find,
like, a really great dress?

944
01:12:02,449 --> 01:12:04,951
[PEOPLE YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

945
01:12:12,126 --> 01:12:18,965
God created man in the form of himself,
not in the form of monkeys!

946
01:12:20,301 --> 01:12:22,469
MAN 1: The Lord is God!
MAN 2: Praise God.

947
01:12:22,636 --> 01:12:26,847
MAN 3: Praise the Lord!
MAN 4: You're wasting my tax dollars!

948
01:12:27,641 --> 01:12:31,268
Get a job.
Don't waste my tax dollars.

949
01:12:31,435 --> 01:12:33,186
You hear me?

950
01:12:52,164 --> 01:12:53,957
Wow.

951
01:12:56,502 --> 01:12:58,170
You look beautiful, Ellie.

952
01:12:59,840 --> 01:13:02,173
- So do you.
- You really do.

953
01:13:05,845 --> 01:13:07,304
I read your book.

954
01:13:08,265 --> 01:13:09,765
Here we go.

955
01:13:09,932 --> 01:13:12,016
Would you like me to quote you?

956
01:13:12,185 --> 01:13:17,189
"Ironically, the thing that people
are most hungry for, meaning...

957
01:13:17,356 --> 01:13:20,693
...is the one thing that science
hasn't been able to give them."

958
01:13:20,860 --> 01:13:23,737
Yeah. Yeah.

959
01:13:24,363 --> 01:13:29,159
Come on. It's like you're saying
that science killed God.

960
01:13:29,327 --> 01:13:32,537
What if science simply revealed...

961
01:13:32,706 --> 01:13:35,207
...that he never existed
in the first place?

962
01:13:38,545 --> 01:13:41,713
- I think we're gonna need to get some air.
- What?

963
01:13:41,881 --> 01:13:43,716
And a few more of these.

964
01:13:45,135 --> 01:13:47,386
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

965
01:13:48,387 --> 01:13:51,556
- A little chilly out here.
- Yeah, this is nice.

966
01:13:51,725 --> 01:13:53,099
- I got one for you.
- What?

967
01:13:53,266 --> 01:13:55,018
Occam's razor. Ever heard of it?

968
01:13:55,226 --> 01:13:57,895
Hoccam's razor.
Sounds like some slasher movie.

969
01:13:58,063 --> 01:14:01,649
No, Occam's Razor.
It's a basic scientific principle. It says...

970
01:14:01,817 --> 01:14:05,403
...all things being equal, the simplest
explanation tends to be the right one.

971
01:14:05,570 --> 01:14:07,197
- Makes sense to me.
- All right.

972
01:14:07,363 --> 01:14:10,158
- So, what's more likely? Thank you.
- You're welcome.

973
01:14:10,326 --> 01:14:12,952
An all-powerful, mysterious God
created the universe...

974
01:14:13,162 --> 01:14:15,997
...and then decided not to give
any proof of his existence?

975
01:14:16,164 --> 01:14:21,002
Or that he simply doesn't exist at all
and that we created him...

976
01:14:21,170 --> 01:14:23,671
...so we wouldn't have to feel
so small and alone.

977
01:14:24,590 --> 01:14:25,840
I don't know.

978
01:14:26,007 --> 01:14:30,011
I couldn't imagine living in a world
where God didn't exist.

979
01:14:30,679 --> 01:14:32,346
I wouldn't want to.

980
01:14:33,015 --> 01:14:35,432
How do you know that
you're not deluding yourself?

981
01:14:36,100 --> 01:14:39,354
I mean, for me, I'd need proof.

982
01:14:40,189 --> 01:14:41,689
Proof?

983
01:14:44,568 --> 01:14:47,069
- Did you love your father?
- What?

984
01:14:47,238 --> 01:14:49,029
Your dad, did you love him?

985
01:14:50,032 --> 01:14:52,867
Yes. Very much.

986
01:14:55,703 --> 01:14:57,247
Prove it.

987
01:15:00,042 --> 01:15:01,960
[PHONE RINGS]

988
01:15:03,753 --> 01:15:04,796
Kent.

989
01:15:04,963 --> 01:15:05,963
[PAGER BEEPING]

990
01:15:06,131 --> 01:15:09,132
- The White House.
- Mr. Joss.

991
01:15:10,301 --> 01:15:13,262
DRUMLIN: I don't want excuses.
Whoever is responsible, I want their head.

992
01:15:13,430 --> 01:15:16,390
- Ellie?
- What happened?

993
01:15:16,557 --> 01:15:17,975
You were right all along.

994
01:15:18,141 --> 01:15:21,270
The decryption team at the VLA
has been working around the clock...

995
01:15:21,436 --> 01:15:24,146
...and the hard work has finally paid off.

996
01:15:24,314 --> 01:15:28,277
This key section, uncovered tonight
and obtained exclusively by CNN...

997
01:15:28,444 --> 01:15:31,070
...shows an illustration
of what is of a human figure...

998
01:15:31,238 --> 01:15:34,073
...inside a geometric structure
of some kind.

999
01:15:34,242 --> 01:15:36,076
This and other contextual clues...

1000
01:15:36,243 --> 01:15:39,328
...now lead scientists to believe
that the message is, in fact...

1001
01:15:39,497 --> 01:15:43,041
- President called an emergency meeting.
- Yeah, I imagine he would.

1002
01:15:43,208 --> 01:15:46,336
- Designed to take
a single human occupant into space...

1003
01:15:46,503 --> 01:15:49,171
...presumably to the star Vega.

1004
01:16:07,692 --> 01:16:09,650
MAN: I'm gonna miss
my mother's birthday party.

1005
01:16:09,819 --> 01:16:12,695
KITZ: Call her in the morning,
tell her why you didn't show up.

1006
01:16:12,863 --> 01:16:14,363
Tell me.

1007
01:16:14,532 --> 01:16:15,657
They're gonna build it.

1008
01:16:15,824 --> 01:16:16,867
Who gets to go?

1009
01:16:17,034 --> 01:16:20,369
The president's just gone international
to spread the risk and cost...

1010
01:16:20,537 --> 01:16:22,079
Who gets to go, though?

1011
01:16:22,247 --> 01:16:23,873
Well, it's complicated, Ellie.

1012
01:16:24,792 --> 01:16:25,833
What?

1013
01:16:26,002 --> 01:16:28,837
They have formed a group
of international candidates.

1014
01:16:29,005 --> 01:16:31,047
Now, it's your discovery.

1015
01:16:31,466 --> 01:16:35,344
Okay, they understand that.
You're at the top of a very short list.

1016
01:16:35,511 --> 01:16:38,055
But they're also putting together
a selection committee.

1017
01:16:38,221 --> 01:16:42,390
It's made of scholars, theologians,
scientists, philosophers...

1018
01:16:42,559 --> 01:16:43,559
You're on it.

1019
01:16:44,770 --> 01:16:46,061
I've been asked, yes.

1020
01:16:49,024 --> 01:16:50,690
I guess that means...

1021
01:16:51,275 --> 01:16:54,028
...that you're a selector,
I'm a selectee and we can't...

1022
01:16:54,195 --> 01:16:55,529
Yeah.

1023
01:16:55,697 --> 01:16:58,114
What you don't understand, Ellie, is...

1024
01:16:58,283 --> 01:17:00,408
- I understand.
- Ellie...

1025
01:17:01,036 --> 01:17:05,372
I want you to know, whatever happens,
as far as I'm concerned...

1026
01:17:05,957 --> 01:17:07,457
Well...

1027
01:17:08,627 --> 01:17:10,211
...good luck.

1028
01:17:14,216 --> 01:17:17,676
Well, whatever you do, make sure
he doesn't monopolize the committee.

1029
01:17:17,844 --> 01:17:19,929
He is not on the committee, Ellie.

1030
01:17:21,681 --> 01:17:23,099
What?

1031
01:17:23,891 --> 01:17:26,935
He just resigned as science advisor.
He wants to be the one to go.

1032
01:17:29,146 --> 01:17:32,440
MAN [ON TV]: The president is already
beginning to feel the financial pinch.

1033
01:17:32,734 --> 01:17:34,819
Sources say the cost of the project...

1034
01:17:34,985 --> 01:17:38,613
...is spiraling
to more than a third of a trillion dollars...

1035
01:17:38,782 --> 01:17:42,368
...making this what may be
the most expensive single project...

1036
01:17:42,577 --> 01:17:44,453
...in all of human history.

1037
01:17:44,662 --> 01:17:47,997
Meanwhile, months of debate finally
reached a conclusion last week...

1038
01:17:48,166 --> 01:17:51,292
...as 10 candidates
were selected by the IMC...

1039
01:17:51,461 --> 01:17:55,422
...representing a cross section of
political, philosophical and religious views.

1040
01:17:55,631 --> 01:17:58,509
Many of these are the same experts
who have been consulting...

1041
01:17:58,676 --> 01:18:00,720
...on the Machine's design and function.

1042
01:18:00,929 --> 01:18:05,140
They will be actively participating on-site
during the construction process.

1043
01:18:05,306 --> 01:18:08,643
But the choice of these 10 candidates
has not been without controversy.

1044
01:18:08,810 --> 01:18:11,645
Fully one-third of the candidates
are American.

1045
01:18:11,814 --> 01:18:14,565
Many international observers
are asking why.

1046
01:18:14,734 --> 01:18:17,860
The U.S. Is shouldering an
enormous percentage of the financial...

1047
01:18:18,069 --> 01:18:21,029
Isn't it true that the contractors,
like Hadden Industries...

1048
01:18:21,239 --> 01:18:24,576
...are making those contributions
in exchange for technology rights?

1049
01:18:24,784 --> 01:18:28,287
Different nations are being compensated
in different ways. For example...

1050
01:18:28,456 --> 01:18:33,001
Japan made headlines when it announced it
would forego candidate representation...

1051
01:18:33,168 --> 01:18:36,378
...in exchange for the systems integration
subcontract.

1052
01:18:36,546 --> 01:18:41,509
On what basis do you choose
a human being to represent humanity?

1053
01:18:41,719 --> 01:18:42,926
Good question, Larry.

1054
01:18:43,095 --> 01:18:45,054
Yes, well, if nothing else...

1055
01:18:45,221 --> 01:18:49,225
...it should be somebody who is fluent in
the language the message was given in.

1056
01:18:49,393 --> 01:18:50,601
Science, in this case.

1057
01:18:51,228 --> 01:18:53,645
Doctor Arroway,
despite your obvious enthusiasm...

1058
01:18:53,855 --> 01:18:56,064
...there's been a lot of criticism of late...

1059
01:18:56,317 --> 01:18:58,818
...that this whole endeavor
is simply too dangerous.

1060
01:18:58,985 --> 01:19:01,570
Some of that criticism from scientists.

1061
01:19:01,780 --> 01:19:04,573
One Nobel Prize winner recently noted,
his words:

1062
01:19:05,367 --> 01:19:07,076
"There is every indication...

1063
01:19:07,286 --> 01:19:11,079
...that this is simply beyond our capabilities,
that this endeavor will fail...

1064
01:19:11,289 --> 01:19:14,917
...and that the Machine's occupant
will pay for that failure with their life."

1065
01:19:15,085 --> 01:19:16,752
How do you respond to that?

1066
01:19:16,962 --> 01:19:20,340
ELLIE: Well, this message is from
a civilization that may be anywhere...

1067
01:19:20,548 --> 01:19:24,260
...from hundreds to millions
and millions of years ahead of us.

1068
01:19:24,511 --> 01:19:27,679
I have to believe that
an intelligence that advanced...

1069
01:19:28,305 --> 01:19:30,306
...knows what they're doing.

1070
01:19:31,225 --> 01:19:35,186
Now all it requires on our part is...

1071
01:19:35,354 --> 01:19:36,395
Faith?

1072
01:19:39,484 --> 01:19:41,568
I was gonna say a sense of adventure.

1073
01:19:41,778 --> 01:19:42,985
MAN:
And in breaking news...

1074
01:19:43,570 --> 01:19:44,863
...a former astronaut...

1075
01:19:45,073 --> 01:19:48,908
...considered to be the leading American
candidate for the Machine seat...

1076
01:19:49,118 --> 01:19:51,411
...has unexpectedly dropped out
of the running.

1077
01:19:51,829 --> 01:19:54,914
Russell met with reporters this afternoon
at his Houston home.

1078
01:19:55,250 --> 01:19:59,211
I told my dad
that I didn't want him to go.

1079
01:19:59,420 --> 01:20:01,128
Daddy, don't go.

1080
01:20:03,800 --> 01:20:06,885
Nothing would give me more pride
than to...

1081
01:20:07,554 --> 01:20:09,555
...represent my country.

1082
01:20:09,721 --> 01:20:11,931
But what can I say to this?

1083
01:20:12,516 --> 01:20:16,353
Consortium officials had no comment,
but sources within the delegation...

1084
01:20:16,520 --> 01:20:18,521
...have disclosed that Dr. Arroway...

1085
01:20:18,689 --> 01:20:22,775
...appears to now be the front-runner
for the Machine seat.

1086
01:20:23,610 --> 01:20:25,988
ELLIE:
"Meet me at noon. Must talk."

1087
01:20:26,154 --> 01:20:28,907
I didn't expect to be getting
a message like this from you.

1088
01:20:29,074 --> 01:20:30,283
Thanks for coming.

1089
01:20:30,493 --> 01:20:33,453
So is this kosher?
Fraternizing with the enemy?

1090
01:20:33,621 --> 01:20:37,123
Selectors and selectees mingling around?

1091
01:20:37,292 --> 01:20:39,458
Can we talk about Einstein?

1092
01:20:39,627 --> 01:20:41,795
Yeah, sure. Okay.

1093
01:20:41,962 --> 01:20:43,380
- Special relativity.
- Yeah.

1094
01:20:43,547 --> 01:20:45,172
This machine...

1095
01:20:45,757 --> 01:20:50,677
...now, if it works, and you travel to Vega
at even close to the speed of light...

1096
01:20:50,845 --> 01:20:53,346
...when you come back...
- If you come back.

1097
01:20:55,516 --> 01:20:57,518
If you come back...

1098
01:20:57,685 --> 01:21:01,980
...you'll only be 4 years older, but over
50 years would have passed here on Earth.

1099
01:21:02,149 --> 01:21:03,858
Basically, yeah.

1100
01:21:04,359 --> 01:21:06,944
And everybody that you care about...

1101
01:21:07,820 --> 01:21:10,155
...will be gone, dead and buried.

1102
01:21:10,990 --> 01:21:14,993
If you came back,
if you survived at all, which...

1103
01:21:16,329 --> 01:21:20,041
Look, Palmer, nobody's saying
this isn't dangerous, all right?

1104
01:21:20,207 --> 01:21:24,337
The rest of the candidates and myself,
we fully understand the risks we're taking.

1105
01:21:24,503 --> 01:21:25,755
Why?

1106
01:21:25,922 --> 01:21:28,632
Because it's a historic opportunity.
The world needs...

1107
01:21:28,841 --> 01:21:31,469
No, you, Ellie. You. You personally.

1108
01:21:32,511 --> 01:21:35,305
By doing this,
you're willing to give your life.

1109
01:21:35,515 --> 01:21:37,682
You're willing to die for it.

1110
01:21:39,519 --> 01:21:40,810
Why?

1111
01:21:44,524 --> 01:21:48,234
From as long as I can remember,
I've been searching for...

1112
01:21:48,862 --> 01:21:50,529
...something...

1113
01:21:50,738 --> 01:21:54,533
...some reason why we're here.
What are we doing here? Who are we?

1114
01:21:55,534 --> 01:21:59,412
If this is a chance to find out
even just a little part of that answer...

1115
01:22:00,916 --> 01:22:03,917
I don't know,
I think it's won'th a human life.

1116
01:22:04,586 --> 01:22:06,127
Don't you?

1117
01:22:12,636 --> 01:22:15,261
You're an incredibly brave woman, Ellie.

1118
01:22:18,056 --> 01:22:20,182
Or incredibly nuts.

1119
01:22:42,247 --> 01:22:43,747
Palmer...

1120
01:22:49,462 --> 01:22:51,547
I'm really confused.

1121
01:22:52,841 --> 01:22:54,091
So am I.

1122
01:22:55,344 --> 01:22:58,930
I think I speak for us all
when I thank you for your patience.

1123
01:22:59,140 --> 01:23:02,600
Myself, I have one final question,
Dr. Arroway.

1124
01:23:04,103 --> 01:23:06,438
If you should meet these Vegans...

1125
01:23:06,646 --> 01:23:10,942
...and were permitted only
one question to ask of them...

1126
01:23:11,109 --> 01:23:12,777
...what would it be?

1127
01:23:14,238 --> 01:23:16,280
Well, I suppose it would be:

1128
01:23:16,448 --> 01:23:18,115
"How did you do it?

1129
01:23:18,658 --> 01:23:23,121
How did you evolve? How did you
survive this technological adolescence...

1130
01:23:23,288 --> 01:23:25,206
...without destroying yourself?"

1131
01:23:25,957 --> 01:23:30,837
That more than any other question is one
I personally would like to have answered.

1132
01:23:31,171 --> 01:23:33,006
Not too bad, Mike.

1133
01:23:33,673 --> 01:23:34,966
PATEL:
I join Dr. Bergeron...

1134
01:23:35,134 --> 01:23:38,594
...in expressing thanks for
your patience, Dr. Arroway.

1135
01:23:38,802 --> 01:23:41,305
We've all been most impressed
with your candor...

1136
01:23:41,472 --> 01:23:43,515
...and your stamina.

1137
01:23:43,682 --> 01:23:46,851
I believe we are ready to move on
to your final statement.

1138
01:23:47,020 --> 01:23:48,936
Madam Chairman,
I have one more question.

1139
01:23:49,104 --> 01:23:50,855
Yes, Mr. Joss.

1140
01:23:51,483 --> 01:23:53,484
Dr. Arroway...

1141
01:23:54,860 --> 01:23:57,195
Would you consider yourself...

1142
01:23:57,697 --> 01:24:00,323
...a spiritual person?

1143
01:24:02,993 --> 01:24:04,744
Uh...

1144
01:24:05,497 --> 01:24:08,832
I don't really understand
the point of the question.

1145
01:24:09,000 --> 01:24:11,877
I consider myself a moral person.

1146
01:24:12,045 --> 01:24:14,003
PATEL:
I'm sure we all agree that is the case...

1147
01:24:14,171 --> 01:24:16,672
...but I think what Mr. Joss
is in fact asking...

1148
01:24:16,841 --> 01:24:18,675
Do you believe in God...

1149
01:24:20,677 --> 01:24:22,679
...Dr. Arroway?

1150
01:24:27,185 --> 01:24:29,603
As a scientist...

1151
01:24:29,770 --> 01:24:33,231
...I rely on empirical evidence,
and in this matter...

1152
01:24:33,399 --> 01:24:37,110
...I don't believe
that there is data either way.

1153
01:24:37,694 --> 01:24:42,115
PATEL: So your answer would in fact be
that you don't believe in God.

1154
01:24:45,537 --> 01:24:48,579
I don't understand the relevance
of the question.

1155
01:24:49,289 --> 01:24:54,418
Dr. Arroway,
95 percent of the world's population...

1156
01:24:54,587 --> 01:24:58,548
...believes in a supreme being
in one form or another.

1157
01:24:59,716 --> 01:25:02,926
I believe that makes the question
more than relevant.

1158
01:25:05,596 --> 01:25:07,305
PATEL:
Dr. Arroway?

1159
01:25:17,234 --> 01:25:19,234
I believe, um...

1160
01:25:23,239 --> 01:25:25,740
I believe I've already
answered that question.

1161
01:25:29,787 --> 01:25:33,291
I'm proud of what
we've achieved as a species...

1162
01:25:33,457 --> 01:25:35,458
...and as a civilization.

1163
01:25:37,128 --> 01:25:39,630
I would hate to see
everything we stand for...

1164
01:25:39,797 --> 01:25:43,717
...all that we have fought for
for a thousand generations...

1165
01:25:43,926 --> 01:25:46,261
...all that God has blessed us with...

1166
01:25:47,597 --> 01:25:49,140
...betrayed...

1167
01:25:50,100 --> 01:25:54,686
...in the final hour because we chose to
send a representative who did not put our...

1168
01:25:55,189 --> 01:25:57,981
...most cherished beliefs first.

1169
01:26:01,278 --> 01:26:02,444
Thank you.

1170
01:26:08,618 --> 01:26:10,953
[KNOCKING]

1171
01:26:35,685 --> 01:26:36,978
Why did you do it?

1172
01:26:41,567 --> 01:26:45,737
Our job was to select someone
to speak for everybody.

1173
01:26:49,033 --> 01:26:52,493
I just couldn't in good conscience
vote for a person...

1174
01:26:52,662 --> 01:26:54,662
...who doesn't believe in God.

1175
01:26:56,707 --> 01:26:58,082
Someone who...

1176
01:26:58,251 --> 01:27:01,670
...honestly thinks
the other 95 percent of us...

1177
01:27:01,878 --> 01:27:04,838
...suffer from some form
of mass delusion.

1178
01:27:08,010 --> 01:27:10,095
I told the truth up there.

1179
01:27:11,389 --> 01:27:14,890
And Drumlin told you exactly
what you wanted to hear.

1180
01:27:50,051 --> 01:27:52,636
DRUMLIN:
With full humility and utmost gratitude...

1181
01:27:52,804 --> 01:27:55,014
...I accept this great honor...

1182
01:27:55,222 --> 01:27:59,268
...and I promise I will do my best
to represent my nation...

1183
01:27:59,435 --> 01:28:04,564
...my planet and my God
on this historic journey.

1184
01:28:04,733 --> 01:28:07,067
I thank you from the bottom of my heart.

1185
01:28:07,234 --> 01:28:10,194
[APPLAUDING]

1186
01:28:49,652 --> 01:28:52,613
MAN [ON TV]: There's
a carnival atmosphere at Cape Canaveral...

1187
01:28:52,780 --> 01:28:54,823
...as the International
Machine Consortium...

1188
01:28:54,990 --> 01:28:58,452
...hosts as much a media event
as a systems test.

1189
01:28:58,953 --> 01:29:02,622
David Drumlin is supervising
the on-site portion of the test.

1190
01:29:02,832 --> 01:29:04,625
We spoke with him earlier today.

1191
01:29:04,792 --> 01:29:07,293
DRUMLIN: We'll be able to monjtor
the stresses and effects...

1192
01:29:07,462 --> 01:29:09,796
...using the robot passenger...

1193
01:29:10,297 --> 01:29:12,591
...who we lovingly call Elmer.

1194
01:29:12,757 --> 01:29:15,885
WOMAN [OVER SPEAKER]: We are coming up
on T-minus two hours and counting.

1195
01:29:16,052 --> 01:29:18,095
All Machine systems are go.

1196
01:29:18,262 --> 01:29:21,140
Dr. Arroway, the press would like to
ask you a few questions...

1197
01:29:21,307 --> 01:29:23,975
...as soon as they're done
with Dr. Drumlin.

1198
01:29:25,270 --> 01:29:27,521
DRUMLIN: Now, at the moment
where we release the pod...

1199
01:29:27,689 --> 01:29:31,274
...there will be a substantial
amount of energy generated at the core.

1200
01:29:31,777 --> 01:29:34,153
We'll be able to monitor
the stresses and effects...

1201
01:29:34,320 --> 01:29:38,490
...using our robot passenger,
who we lovingly call Elmer.

1202
01:29:38,658 --> 01:29:39,826
[CHUCKLES]

1203
01:29:39,993 --> 01:29:41,618
- Thank you.
- Welcome.

1204
01:29:41,787 --> 01:29:43,703
WOMAN:
- The test area is clear and go.

1205
01:29:43,872 --> 01:29:46,666
Sir, they're ready for you out at the site.

1206
01:29:46,833 --> 01:29:48,458
Yeah, just a minute.

1207
01:29:49,502 --> 01:29:52,796
WOMAN: The test director has issued a go
to enter the final countdown phase.

1208
01:29:52,965 --> 01:29:54,297
Ellie.

1209
01:29:54,466 --> 01:29:56,842
- Congratulations, David.
- Glad you could come.

1210
01:29:58,177 --> 01:30:00,637
Didrt, uh, expect to see you here.

1211
01:30:01,347 --> 01:30:06,185
Well, I'm still, you know,
Crew Ops at the Control Center.

1212
01:30:06,854 --> 01:30:10,856
And I suppose the fact that I discovered
the message means that I have PR value.

1213
01:30:11,024 --> 01:30:12,692
Of course.

1214
01:30:14,194 --> 01:30:17,363
Ellie, I know you must think
this is all very unfair.

1215
01:30:18,030 --> 01:30:20,323
And maybe that's an understatement.

1216
01:30:21,409 --> 01:30:23,786
What you don't know is, I agree.

1217
01:30:24,371 --> 01:30:27,664
I wish the world was a place
where fair was the bottom line.

1218
01:30:27,832 --> 01:30:31,042
Where the kind of idealism you showed
at the hearing was rewarded...

1219
01:30:31,211 --> 01:30:33,503
...not taken advantage of.

1220
01:30:35,215 --> 01:30:38,341
Unfortunately,
we don't live in that world.

1221
01:30:40,386 --> 01:30:41,886
Funny...

1222
01:30:42,930 --> 01:30:46,390
...I always believed that the world
is what we make of it.

1223
01:30:48,060 --> 01:30:51,229
Excuse me, Dr. Drumlin, sir?

1224
01:30:52,856 --> 01:30:54,399
Good luck on the test.

1225
01:30:54,649 --> 01:30:56,984
- The pad leader has issued the order...
- Thank you.

1226
01:30:57,153 --> 01:31:00,322
...to clear the pad of all nonessential...
- Right this way, sir.

1227
01:31:04,827 --> 01:31:08,704
Test director, everything looks good
up here. We're ready to go.

1228
01:31:08,872 --> 01:31:11,875
STEVE: All right, people, I want
things double and triple checked here.

1229
01:31:12,042 --> 01:31:15,628
We only get one shot at this.
Let's get it right.

1230
01:31:15,796 --> 01:31:18,881
Ladies and gentlemen,
we are ready for startup.

1231
01:31:19,091 --> 01:31:22,426
All controllers, I need a go-no-go
for test initiation.

1232
01:31:22,595 --> 01:31:23,595
- Mechanical?
MAN 1: Go.

1233
01:31:23,762 --> 01:31:24,804
- Electrical?
MAN 2: Go.

1234
01:31:24,971 --> 01:31:26,055
- Dynamics?
MAN 3: Go.

1235
01:31:26,224 --> 01:31:27,515
- Communications?
MAN 4: Go.

1236
01:31:27,682 --> 01:31:28,725
- Pod systems?
WOMAN: Go

1237
01:31:28,893 --> 01:31:30,435
- Safety?
MAN 5: Go.

1238
01:31:30,603 --> 01:31:33,521
Crew Ops, verify all pre-test
procedures are complete.

1239
01:31:33,689 --> 01:31:35,105
Yes, verified. I'm go.

1240
01:31:35,274 --> 01:31:37,775
Pad leader, we are good.
Is everything okay with you?

1241
01:31:37,944 --> 01:31:40,612
Roger. The pad is a go.

1242
01:31:40,779 --> 01:31:43,614
STEVE:
Test initiation, on my mark.

1243
01:31:44,074 --> 01:31:45,449
Five...

1244
01:31:45,618 --> 01:31:46,868
...four...

1245
01:31:47,036 --> 01:31:48,328
...three...

1246
01:31:48,496 --> 01:31:49,703
...two...

1247
01:31:50,122 --> 01:31:51,622
...one.

1248
01:31:51,791 --> 01:31:53,207
Mark.

1249
01:31:53,376 --> 01:31:55,126
MAN 1: Test start.
MAN 2: Rings are unlocked.

1250
01:31:55,293 --> 01:31:57,045
MAN 3:
Power levels indicate a good start.

1251
01:31:57,212 --> 01:32:00,088
WOMAN 1: We have begun the full-scale
test of Earth's first system...

1252
01:32:00,256 --> 01:32:03,801
...built by the sharing of knowledge
with a neighbor in our universe.

1253
01:32:03,969 --> 01:32:06,220
MAN 4:
All power sources on core induction bus.

1254
01:32:06,387 --> 01:32:08,012
WOMAN 2:
IPV power transfer.

1255
01:32:08,180 --> 01:32:11,934
GERRY: Ring motion detect.
Alpha, Bravo, Charlie.

1256
01:32:12,978 --> 01:32:16,020
STEVE: Gerry, how are we looking?
GERRY: Looks good. We're underway.

1257
01:32:16,189 --> 01:32:17,939
DRUMLIN:
Looks like we have a normal startup.

1258
01:32:18,108 --> 01:32:20,650
STEVE:
Roger, David. It's looking good here.

1259
01:32:20,819 --> 01:32:23,069
[CHEERING]

1260
01:32:26,283 --> 01:32:29,409
WOMAN 1: We are moments away from
the initiation of the drop sequence.

1261
01:32:29,578 --> 01:32:31,578
All systems are go.

1262
01:32:33,707 --> 01:32:36,332
STEVE: Mechanical, you still happy?
MAN 1: Roger that.

1263
01:32:36,501 --> 01:32:39,962
DRUMLIN: I'll tell you, this is very exciting
from up here.

1264
01:32:42,131 --> 01:32:45,759
GERRY: We've got 4 percent.
DRUMLIN: We're confirming 4 percent.

1265
01:32:47,011 --> 01:32:50,346
Frequency 9.85.

1266
01:32:50,515 --> 01:32:56,270
Harmonics in the green. G-level 1.1.

1267
01:32:56,438 --> 01:32:59,773
- Five percent.
- Confirmed. We are at 5 percent.

1268
01:32:59,940 --> 01:33:01,692
David, how's it looking to you?

1269
01:33:01,859 --> 01:33:04,694
DRUMLIN: Okay. I'm gonna take a look
and show you what we got.

1270
01:33:04,863 --> 01:33:07,030
MAN 2: All test-subject instrumentation
looks good.

1271
01:33:07,198 --> 01:33:10,868
Confirmed, we have a good picture
from Dr. Drumlirs PRD.

1272
01:33:11,036 --> 01:33:13,494
DRUMLIN: Hope you guys are seeing
what I'm seeing.

1273
01:33:13,872 --> 01:33:15,788
MAN 3:
All systems are go.

1274
01:33:17,375 --> 01:33:18,958
DRUMLIN:
This is really something.

1275
01:33:19,168 --> 01:33:20,836
MAN 4:
For purposes of this test...

1276
01:33:21,003 --> 01:33:25,213
...Dr. Drumlin will be on top of
the gantry crane that's over the Machine.

1277
01:33:25,381 --> 01:33:27,550
We've got some video animation...

1278
01:33:27,717 --> 01:33:31,220
...to show you just how this machine,
it is thought, will work.

1279
01:33:31,387 --> 01:33:33,055
The passenger pod will be released.

1280
01:33:33,265 --> 01:33:37,601
It will come down through the center of
the rings and into the Machine's core.

1281
01:33:37,770 --> 01:33:41,855
The big question everyone here is asking is,
of course, what happens then?

1282
01:33:42,024 --> 01:33:46,860
Some believe that the rings function as
some sort of an accelerator or something...

1283
01:33:47,029 --> 01:33:49,655
...sending its energy
into this passenger pod...

1284
01:33:49,823 --> 01:33:52,533
...making it rocket away
at near the speed of light.

1285
01:33:52,743 --> 01:33:57,372
Other people believe it might open up
a doorway to some other dimension.

1286
01:33:57,538 --> 01:34:01,000
Who's right?
Well, that's what today's test is all about.

1287
01:34:01,627 --> 01:34:04,087
GERRY: Thirty-five percent.
MAN 1: Subsystems, are you ready?

1288
01:34:04,253 --> 01:34:07,422
GERRY: Forty percent normal acceleration.
MAN 2: Roger, confirm 40 percent.

1289
01:34:07,632 --> 01:34:10,592
STEVE: All controllers stand by
to initiate drop sequence...

1290
01:34:10,761 --> 01:34:12,345
...on my mark.

1291
01:34:12,512 --> 01:34:14,846
MAN 3:
All systems ready for drop sequence.

1292
01:34:15,015 --> 01:34:17,265
GERRY:
Forty-five percent.

1293
01:34:17,434 --> 01:34:19,601
DRUMLIN:
We're reading 45 percent.

1294
01:34:20,604 --> 01:34:22,604
Can you verify closure?

1295
01:34:23,899 --> 01:34:25,440
GERRY:
Forty-six.

1296
01:34:25,609 --> 01:34:30,279
STEVE: All controllers stand by
to initiate IPV drop sequence. On my mark.

1297
01:34:30,948 --> 01:34:32,698
GERRY:
Forty-eight percent.

1298
01:34:33,324 --> 01:34:35,743
DRUMLIN: Test djrector,
I'm feeling a very strange vibration.

1299
01:34:35,911 --> 01:34:37,119
Are you feeling it down there?

1300
01:34:37,287 --> 01:34:39,247
STEVE:
Gerry, can you confirm any vibration?

1301
01:34:39,789 --> 01:34:41,623
GERRY:
Negative, everything looks good here.

1302
01:34:41,792 --> 01:34:43,792
- Crew Ops?
- Nothing wrong with Elmer.

1303
01:34:43,961 --> 01:34:45,795
We're not seeing anything abnormal.

1304
01:34:45,962 --> 01:34:48,755
DRUMLIN: No good. Hold the sequence.
I'm gonna take a direct reading.

1305
01:34:49,256 --> 01:34:52,634
STEVE: What the hell is he talking about?
- Can anyone say grandstanding?

1306
01:34:52,801 --> 01:34:54,802
He sure knows he's on TV!

1307
01:34:54,970 --> 01:34:58,097
Back home that's what we call
an overcooked ham.

1308
01:34:58,265 --> 01:35:00,766
DRUMLIN:
I'm reading 10 kilohertz!

1309
01:35:00,935 --> 01:35:03,729
What's your reading on the first
and second order G-levels?

1310
01:35:03,938 --> 01:35:05,814
MAN 1:
G-levels are right on.

1311
01:35:06,314 --> 01:35:09,818
MAN 2: We confirm Drumlirs readings
and they're all normal. We're go.

1312
01:35:09,985 --> 01:35:11,485
STEVE:
Copy that, Dynamics.

1313
01:35:11,654 --> 01:35:14,405
I think we're okay,
but we'll let him finish.

1314
01:35:15,615 --> 01:35:17,658
- Mechanical, you still okay?
MAN 3: Roger, chief.

1315
01:35:17,827 --> 01:35:19,161
We're right on the money.

1316
01:35:19,328 --> 01:35:21,621
We've got a security problem here.

1317
01:35:21,788 --> 01:35:23,372
Ellie, are you sure?

1318
01:35:23,541 --> 01:35:25,833
Yeah. This guy, he shouldn't be there.
I know him.

1319
01:35:26,002 --> 01:35:28,962
Gerry, execute the
rapid shutdown sequence.

1320
01:35:29,130 --> 01:35:32,423
Security, move emergency
response team into position one.

1321
01:35:32,591 --> 01:35:35,176
- Get me Drumlin on a secure loop, please.
- You got him.

1322
01:35:35,344 --> 01:35:38,846
- David, can you hear me?
DRUMLIN: Yes, I hear.

1323
01:35:39,015 --> 01:35:41,307
ELLIE: All right, we've got
a security breach here.

1324
01:35:41,684 --> 01:35:43,685
Right behind you. The tall guy.

1325
01:35:44,186 --> 01:35:47,439
The technician. See him?

1326
01:35:49,484 --> 01:35:51,859
He's not supposed to be there.

1327
01:35:56,532 --> 01:35:59,201
David, he's got something in his hand!

1328
01:35:59,368 --> 01:36:01,912
Him! Take him! Security breach!

1329
01:36:02,579 --> 01:36:03,704
He's got a bomb!

1330
01:36:03,872 --> 01:36:06,500
STEVE: I want that emergency-response
team up on the gantry now.

1331
01:36:06,667 --> 01:36:08,335
Security, stage one alert.

1332
01:36:08,502 --> 01:36:13,005
By God, move all the fire and
rescue personnel into position one.

1333
01:36:13,840 --> 01:36:15,673
[YELLING]

1334
01:36:29,021 --> 01:36:31,564
[SCREAMING]

1335
01:36:49,583 --> 01:36:51,710
STEVE:
All right, all right, back to your stations.

1336
01:36:51,877 --> 01:36:55,005
I need you to be professional, people.
Settle down.

1337
01:36:55,215 --> 01:36:58,091
Pad leader, pad leader, do you copy?

1338
01:37:15,527 --> 01:37:18,194
The scene earlier today,
when David Drumlin...

1339
01:37:18,404 --> 01:37:20,113
...advisor to two presidents...

1340
01:37:20,282 --> 01:37:24,284
...and winner of the National Academy
of Sciences lifetime award...

1341
01:37:24,452 --> 01:37:28,247
...was laid to rest
at Arlington National Cemetery.

1342
01:37:31,960 --> 01:37:33,877
In a related story, last night's raid...

1343
01:37:34,045 --> 01:37:35,587
Can I help you?

1344
01:37:35,753 --> 01:37:39,798
- Oh, you're... I've got some mail for you.
...resulted in the discovery of this video.

1345
01:37:39,966 --> 01:37:44,679
The suicide note of the leader of the
terrorist group now believed responsible...

1346
01:37:44,846 --> 01:37:47,390
...for the explosion in Florida this week.

1347
01:37:47,557 --> 01:37:52,561
What we do,
we do for the goodness of all mankind.

1348
01:37:53,229 --> 01:37:56,149
This won't be understood, not now...

1349
01:37:56,317 --> 01:37:58,275
...but the apocalypse to come...

1350
01:37:59,444 --> 01:38:01,613
...will vindicate our faith.

1351
01:38:10,747 --> 01:38:14,458
[PULSING]

1352
01:38:25,930 --> 01:38:27,764
Welcome home.

1353
01:39:23,360 --> 01:39:25,654
[MAN SPEAKING IN RUSSIAN
ON TV]

1354
01:39:33,537 --> 01:39:35,913
Oh, Comrade Arroway...

1355
01:39:36,082 --> 01:39:39,376
...he has been expecting your call.
One moment, please.

1356
01:39:49,136 --> 01:39:50,345
Mr. Hadden?

1357
01:39:50,971 --> 01:39:52,305
Doctor.

1358
01:39:53,432 --> 01:39:55,225
How kind of you to call.

1359
01:39:55,935 --> 01:39:58,353
Mr. Hadden, where are you?

1360
01:40:00,064 --> 01:40:04,734
The Russian government was kind enough
to give me accommodations on Mir.

1361
01:40:05,569 --> 01:40:07,445
You're living on a space station?

1362
01:40:08,948 --> 01:40:11,283
It's quite simple, really.

1363
01:40:12,326 --> 01:40:15,912
The low-oxygen,
zero-gravity environment...

1364
01:40:16,079 --> 01:40:20,792
...is the only thing keeping
the cancer from eating me alive.

1365
01:40:22,335 --> 01:40:25,046
Actually, I quite like it up here.

1366
01:40:25,505 --> 01:40:29,300
My little room has one hell of a view.

1367
01:40:36,475 --> 01:40:38,975
I wanna show you something.

1368
01:40:43,148 --> 01:40:45,608
Hokkaido Island.

1369
01:40:46,525 --> 01:40:48,903
The systems integration site.

1370
01:40:49,904 --> 01:40:52,155
Look closer.

1371
01:40:59,789 --> 01:41:03,417
First rule in government spending:

1372
01:41:03,585 --> 01:41:07,505
Why build one when you can have
two at twice the price?

1373
01:41:07,671 --> 01:41:11,466
Only, this one can be kept secret.

1374
01:41:11,635 --> 01:41:13,676
Controlled by Americans...

1375
01:41:13,845 --> 01:41:17,472
...built by the Japanese subcontractors...

1376
01:41:18,182 --> 01:41:21,769
...who also happen to be...

1377
01:41:21,936 --> 01:41:24,020
...recently acquired...

1378
01:41:24,189 --> 01:41:27,315
...wholly-owned subsidiaries...

1379
01:41:27,484 --> 01:41:29,859
...of Hadden Industries.
- Of Hadden Industries.

1380
01:41:33,030 --> 01:41:36,199
They still want
an American to go, doctor.

1381
01:41:39,829 --> 01:41:42,163
Wanna take a ride?

1382
01:42:24,289 --> 01:42:28,585
WOMAN: And augmenting our restraint and
communications console subsystem...

1383
01:42:28,752 --> 01:42:30,752
...we have your personal recording unit.

1384
01:42:30,921 --> 01:42:35,048
Normal, infrared and ultraviolet lenses.

1385
01:42:35,216 --> 01:42:39,261
Digital microchip good for
thousands of hours of recording.

1386
01:42:40,471 --> 01:42:42,556
Okay, look, I understand...

1387
01:42:42,725 --> 01:42:46,144
...the reason for recording
and documenting the mission.

1388
01:42:46,311 --> 01:42:49,146
But I just... I wanna go on record
one more time.

1389
01:42:49,314 --> 01:42:52,817
The transmitted specs
never said anything about any chair...

1390
01:42:53,068 --> 01:42:57,572
...or a restraining harness or survival gear.

1391
01:42:57,739 --> 01:42:59,573
Why can't we just trust the original...?

1392
01:42:59,742 --> 01:43:03,869
Doctor, both the IMC Board
and the SI team reviewed the matter...

1393
01:43:04,078 --> 01:43:07,832
...and concluded that
the design impact is negligible.

1394
01:43:08,000 --> 01:43:09,707
Bottom line is...

1395
01:43:09,876 --> 01:43:12,211
...we're not putting anybody
aboard this machine...

1396
01:43:12,420 --> 01:43:15,421
...unless there is
some sort of minimal protection.

1397
01:43:15,590 --> 01:43:17,466
End of story.

1398
01:43:19,886 --> 01:43:23,137
- Okay.
MAN: Ellie...

1399
01:43:24,015 --> 01:43:28,100
...we've been giving these to the astronauts
since the beginning of the space program.

1400
01:43:29,436 --> 01:43:31,729
It's never been made public, of course.

1401
01:43:31,939 --> 01:43:34,024
It's fast and it's painless.

1402
01:43:36,778 --> 01:43:39,654
I'm gonna travel 26 light years
to commit suicide?

1403
01:43:39,822 --> 01:43:42,032
Something may go wrong.

1404
01:43:42,199 --> 01:43:44,952
There may be
an unforeseen mechanical failure.

1405
01:43:45,703 --> 01:43:48,788
You could be marooned, unable to return.

1406
01:43:49,957 --> 01:43:53,085
There are a thousand reasons
we can think of for you to have this...

1407
01:43:53,293 --> 01:43:56,462
...but mostly it's for the reasons
we can't think of.

1408
01:44:21,530 --> 01:44:22,572
[KNOCKING]

1409
01:44:22,739 --> 01:44:23,864
Come in.

1410
01:44:25,409 --> 01:44:29,412
- Dr. Arroway, time to get ready.
- Thank you.

1411
01:44:40,090 --> 01:44:41,798
I know you don't have much time.

1412
01:44:41,966 --> 01:44:45,051
As soon as I found out about the Machine,
I called the president.

1413
01:44:45,261 --> 01:44:47,345
I came with Kitz.

1414
01:44:47,514 --> 01:44:49,806
I had to see you one more time.

1415
01:44:49,975 --> 01:44:51,725
- Oh, God, I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

1416
01:44:51,893 --> 01:44:53,769
No, I'm glad you came.

1417
01:44:53,936 --> 01:44:56,814
There's something I gotta say to you.

1418
01:44:57,690 --> 01:45:01,944
The reason I didn't vote for you to go was
a good reason, but it wasrt the real one.

1419
01:45:03,029 --> 01:45:05,030
I didn't vote for you to go...

1420
01:45:06,574 --> 01:45:08,743
...because I don't wanna lose you.

1421
01:45:09,786 --> 01:45:12,621
You find your way home, all right?

1422
01:45:29,014 --> 01:45:30,430
Twenty-three hours ago...

1423
01:45:30,599 --> 01:45:34,643
...the world was stunned by the
announcement of a second Machine...

1424
01:45:34,810 --> 01:45:37,938
...and its passenger,
Eleanor Ann Arroway.

1425
01:45:38,148 --> 01:45:41,734
Now the question
that's on everyone's mind:

1426
01:45:41,902 --> 01:45:43,903
Will history repeat itself?

1427
01:45:44,070 --> 01:45:46,363
With a piece of engineering
this complex...

1428
01:45:46,530 --> 01:45:50,618
...with so many unknowns,
could the unthinkable occur?

1429
01:45:50,786 --> 01:45:54,246
The security in Hokkaido
has been incredibly tight.

1430
01:45:54,413 --> 01:45:57,748
No reporters whatsoever
have been allowed near the site.

1431
01:48:19,724 --> 01:48:21,725
Thanks.

1432
01:48:38,283 --> 01:48:41,286
Magnetic restraint is secure.
All life support functions normal.

1433
01:48:41,496 --> 01:48:44,663
Roger that. Ellie, this is Control.
Do you copy?

1434
01:48:44,831 --> 01:48:47,166
Ellie to Control, reading you five-by-five.

1435
01:48:47,333 --> 01:48:51,420
- Comm 1, Give me Ellie's PRD.
- Video unit recording and transmitting.

1436
01:48:52,381 --> 01:48:54,923
- Are you reading me?
STEVE: That's affirmative.

1437
01:48:55,091 --> 01:48:57,385
Video looks good.

1438
01:48:57,552 --> 01:49:00,095
- Copy that, Control.
- Okay.

1439
01:49:00,264 --> 01:49:03,140
Ellie, we're gonna proceed
to button you up.

1440
01:49:03,307 --> 01:49:05,976
Roger, Control. I'm ready.

1441
01:49:09,398 --> 01:49:11,774
- Dynamics...
- I can confirm the walkway retraction.

1442
01:49:11,942 --> 01:49:12,942
STEVE: Systems?
MAN 1: Go.

1443
01:49:13,109 --> 01:49:14,484
STEVE: Communications?
MAN 2: Go.

1444
01:49:14,653 --> 01:49:16,319
STEVE: Life support?
WOMAN: Go.

1445
01:49:16,488 --> 01:49:18,780
Ellie, we are go for closure.

1446
01:49:20,242 --> 01:49:22,118
I'm go here.

1447
01:49:22,994 --> 01:49:26,497
STEVE: Mechanical, initiate
IPV closure sequence.

1448
01:49:28,125 --> 01:49:30,333
Hold on, let me get you a chair.

1449
01:49:31,043 --> 01:49:32,086
ELLIE:
I'm go.

1450
01:49:32,253 --> 01:49:36,131
- It's nice to smell you again, Mr. Kitz.
- You too.

1451
01:49:36,300 --> 01:49:38,134
Wouldrt peg him as a Polo man.

1452
01:49:47,685 --> 01:49:49,020
I got a visual on the door.

1453
01:49:49,186 --> 01:49:51,146
WOMAN:
IPV escape system is armed.

1454
01:49:51,314 --> 01:49:53,315
Door is looking good.

1455
01:49:58,529 --> 01:50:00,197
Door alignment looks good.

1456
01:50:28,809 --> 01:50:30,894
Ellie, we are showing green
across the board.

1457
01:50:31,061 --> 01:50:34,396
Copy that, Control. IPV is secure.

1458
01:50:41,529 --> 01:50:43,530
GERRY:
We are at 30 percent.

1459
01:50:43,698 --> 01:50:44,990
Copy that, 30 percent.

1460
01:50:49,872 --> 01:50:52,539
- How you doing in there, EI?
- Kent?

1461
01:50:53,292 --> 01:50:56,086
- Is that you?
- That's a big affirmative.

1462
01:50:57,003 --> 01:50:58,587
Who let you in there, huh?

1463
01:50:58,756 --> 01:51:00,881
A higher power intervened.

1464
01:51:02,926 --> 01:51:04,260
Well, I'm glad you came.

1465
01:51:09,015 --> 01:51:10,182
GERRY:
Thirty-five percent.

1466
01:51:10,935 --> 01:51:12,435
Copy that, 35 percent.

1467
01:51:12,603 --> 01:51:13,936
- Mechanical?
- We're good.

1468
01:51:14,104 --> 01:51:15,438
Forty percent.

1469
01:51:19,068 --> 01:51:20,944
I'm picking up a moderate vibration here.

1470
01:51:22,113 --> 01:51:25,739
- Dynamics, can you confirm vibration?
GERRY: Everything looks good here.

1471
01:51:25,949 --> 01:51:29,202
She's feeling the same thing
they felt at the Cape at this point.

1472
01:51:29,369 --> 01:51:30,953
Ellie, the vibration is normal.

1473
01:51:31,122 --> 01:51:33,622
GERRY: We are at 50 percent.
All systems nominal.

1474
01:51:33,789 --> 01:51:35,791
Copy that, 50 percent.

1475
01:51:40,963 --> 01:51:42,965
Vibration is getting a little stronger now.

1476
01:51:43,132 --> 01:51:45,967
We're picking up
some low-frequency noise.

1477
01:51:46,344 --> 01:51:49,430
- Mechanical, can you confirm?
- It looks fine to me.

1478
01:51:49,596 --> 01:51:52,975
STEVE: Roger. Gerry, what do you think?
- I'm still go.

1479
01:51:53,143 --> 01:51:54,768
People, we are still go.

1480
01:51:56,520 --> 01:51:58,980
What...? Something's happening.

1481
01:52:00,233 --> 01:52:02,900
I'm... There's...

1482
01:52:03,069 --> 01:52:05,904
There's a light. Do you see that?
I'm seeing some...

1483
01:52:06,655 --> 01:52:09,115
Something, some...

1484
01:52:09,283 --> 01:52:11,827
I can't tell whether it's daylight or not.

1485
01:52:11,994 --> 01:52:14,912
There it is again.
It's coming from the bottom.

1486
01:52:15,957 --> 01:52:17,498
Here, let me show you. See that?

1487
01:52:17,667 --> 01:52:19,585
Negative. Ellie, you're breaking up.

1488
01:52:19,752 --> 01:52:22,587
- Comm 1, can we boost her signal?
- Already at maximum.

1489
01:52:22,756 --> 01:52:24,297
GERRY:
Sixty-five percent.

1490
01:52:24,466 --> 01:52:26,175
The material is changing.

1491
01:52:26,341 --> 01:52:29,845
It's bordering on translucence.
But the system is intact.

1492
01:52:33,140 --> 01:52:37,519
It's gotta be some kind
of electromagnetic field.

1493
01:52:37,686 --> 01:52:40,689
- Are you reading this?
- Negative, we're seeing only interference.

1494
01:52:40,856 --> 01:52:46,194
It's becoming completely translucent.
I can't describe it. I can't even explain it.

1495
01:52:48,655 --> 01:52:49,698
Seventy percent.

1496
01:52:49,865 --> 01:52:52,201
People, we have intermittent comm,
but we are go.

1497
01:52:52,368 --> 01:52:56,828
- Initiate secondary drive systems.
GERRY: Initiating auxiliary booster sequence.

1498
01:52:57,038 --> 01:52:58,872
MAN:
We're go for ignition.

1499
01:53:05,922 --> 01:53:08,381
We have auxiliary booster ignition.

1500
01:53:14,055 --> 01:53:15,555
Life support, how is she doing?

1501
01:53:15,724 --> 01:53:18,975
We still have data. Heart and respiration
are high but within limits.

1502
01:53:19,144 --> 01:53:20,228
Ellie, do you copy?

1503
01:53:20,436 --> 01:53:23,439
If you could hear, I am okay to go.

1504
01:53:27,235 --> 01:53:29,028
If you could hear me...

1505
01:53:32,114 --> 01:53:33,490
Eighty percent.

1506
01:53:33,658 --> 01:53:36,493
All vibration and G-levels are in the green.

1507
01:53:41,917 --> 01:53:44,252
Control, if you're reading me...

1508
01:53:44,418 --> 01:53:46,753
...I am okay to go. Okay to go,

1509
01:53:46,921 --> 01:53:50,716
GERRY: Eighty-five percent.
MAN: All bearing tips are on the profile.

1510
01:53:51,592 --> 01:53:54,679
Ninety percent. We're detecting
some structural instability.

1511
01:53:54,846 --> 01:53:58,765
- Confirmed. Is she holding?
- We're within limits, barely.

1512
01:54:00,269 --> 01:54:06,189
I'm okay to go.

1513
01:54:12,113 --> 01:54:13,573
My God!

1514
01:54:24,625 --> 01:54:27,127
Okay to go. I'm okay.

1515
01:54:27,545 --> 01:54:29,045
Hundred percent target velocity.

1516
01:54:29,212 --> 01:54:30,421
MAN:
Steve?

1517
01:54:30,590 --> 01:54:34,967
Tremendous EMI levels around the Machine.
All field measurements are off-scale.

1518
01:54:35,136 --> 01:54:37,595
Steve, we're approaching our abort limits.

1519
01:54:39,974 --> 01:54:41,056
Okay to go.

1520
01:54:46,271 --> 01:54:47,479
I hear her!

1521
01:54:47,648 --> 01:54:50,483
I hear her. Barely, but she's there.

1522
01:54:50,650 --> 01:54:53,653
- Okay to go.
- She says she's okay to go.

1523
01:54:56,657 --> 01:54:58,783
Steve, we're real close.

1524
01:54:58,951 --> 01:55:01,828
- Electrical, reading in the core?
MAN: Internal environment normal.

1525
01:55:01,996 --> 01:55:04,997
Inside the core, the weather's beautiful.

1526
01:55:09,086 --> 01:55:10,337
I'm okay to go.

1527
01:55:10,837 --> 01:55:14,298
Okay to go. I'm okay to go.

1528
01:55:14,884 --> 01:55:17,217
STEVE:
Initiate drop sequence.

1529
01:55:19,805 --> 01:55:21,514
On my mark.

1530
01:55:22,224 --> 01:55:24,768
Ten, nine...

1531
01:55:25,853 --> 01:55:27,854
...eight...

1532
01:55:28,189 --> 01:55:31,190
...seven, six...

1533
01:55:31,359 --> 01:55:33,984
...five, four...

1534
01:55:34,153 --> 01:55:36,820
...three, two...

1535
01:55:36,988 --> 01:55:38,364
I'm okay to go.

1536
01:55:42,328 --> 01:55:44,118
Oh, God!

1537
01:55:53,380 --> 01:55:55,046
Ellie to Control.

1538
01:55:55,715 --> 01:56:05,765
Ellie to Control, do you read me?

1539
01:56:11,523 --> 01:56:14,942
I'm gonna try to keep recording.

1540
01:56:15,694 --> 01:56:20,238
I'm going through
some kind of a tunnel.

1541
01:56:34,921 --> 01:56:36,462
There's a light source ahead.

1542
01:56:36,965 --> 01:56:40,175
Brilliant and blue-white.

1543
01:56:41,386 --> 01:56:43,011
Residual radiation?

1544
01:56:54,774 --> 01:56:56,065
It's a star.

1545
01:56:56,650 --> 01:57:00,069
I must have gone through a wormhole.

1546
01:57:05,118 --> 01:57:06,534
It's Vega.

1547
01:57:17,755 --> 01:57:19,296
I'm in another wormhole now.

1548
01:57:22,967 --> 01:57:24,092
I had no idea.

1549
01:57:24,261 --> 01:57:26,054
A series of them.

1550
01:57:29,057 --> 01:57:30,307
They're alive.

1551
01:57:30,475 --> 01:57:34,436
It's like some kind of a transit system.

1552
01:57:35,439 --> 01:57:36,814
It's a subway.

1553
01:57:36,981 --> 01:57:38,483
[YELLS]

1554
01:57:42,154 --> 01:57:43,945
Okay.

1555
01:57:44,113 --> 01:57:46,407
Okay, I've gotta keep talking.

1556
01:57:48,952 --> 01:57:52,829
It's a triple... No, quadruple system.

1557
01:57:53,247 --> 01:57:54,498
It's beautiful.

1558
01:57:57,836 --> 01:57:59,252
They're alive.

1559
01:58:07,429 --> 01:58:09,096
Another wormhole!

1560
01:58:09,430 --> 01:58:11,265
This one is much more violent!

1561
01:59:44,692 --> 01:59:46,359
Some...

1562
01:59:46,819 --> 01:59:49,154
...celestial event...

1563
01:59:50,405 --> 01:59:52,114
No...

1564
01:59:52,283 --> 01:59:55,951
No words. No words...

1565
01:59:57,621 --> 01:59:59,829
...to describe it.

1566
02:00:01,248 --> 02:00:03,125
Poetry.

1567
02:00:04,293 --> 02:00:07,796
They should have sent a poet.

1568
02:00:08,088 --> 02:00:10,673
It's so beautiful.

1569
02:00:10,841 --> 02:00:12,301
Beautiful.

1570
02:00:14,136 --> 02:00:19,432
So beautiful.

1571
02:00:20,310 --> 02:00:26,899
I had no idea.

1572
02:00:28,150 --> 02:00:31,487
I had no...

1573
02:00:32,780 --> 02:00:36,074
I had no idea.

1574
02:00:37,409 --> 02:00:44,416
I had no idea. I had no idea.

1575
02:03:02,386 --> 02:03:03,761
Hi, Sparks.

1576
02:03:05,640 --> 02:03:07,140
Dad?

1577
02:03:14,606 --> 02:03:16,483
I missed you.

1578
02:03:22,114 --> 02:03:23,280
Arert you...?

1579
02:03:23,490 --> 02:03:26,701
I'm sorry I couldn't
be there for you, sweetheart.

1580
02:03:36,503 --> 02:03:38,171
You're not real.

1581
02:03:39,673 --> 02:03:41,173
None of this is real.

1582
02:03:41,341 --> 02:03:43,510
That's my scientist.

1583
02:03:44,595 --> 02:03:48,974
When I was unconscious, you downloaded
my thoughts, my memory even.

1584
02:03:49,809 --> 02:03:51,851
Pensacola.

1585
02:03:54,354 --> 02:03:57,314
We thought this might
make things easier for you.

1586
02:04:10,828 --> 02:04:14,457
- Why did you contact us?
- You contacted us.

1587
02:04:14,623 --> 02:04:16,292
We were just listening.

1588
02:04:17,168 --> 02:04:18,461
And there are others?

1589
02:04:18,627 --> 02:04:20,253
Many others.

1590
02:04:25,092 --> 02:04:26,594
They all...

1591
02:04:26,761 --> 02:04:29,889
...travel here through that
transit system that you built?

1592
02:04:30,431 --> 02:04:31,931
We didn't build it.

1593
02:04:33,100 --> 02:04:34,601
We don't know who did.

1594
02:04:36,688 --> 02:04:39,648
No, they were gone
long before we ever got here.

1595
02:04:40,274 --> 02:04:42,109
Maybe someday they'll come back.

1596
02:04:42,944 --> 02:04:45,654
All the other civilizations that you find,
they come here?

1597
02:04:45,863 --> 02:04:47,072
Not all.

1598
02:04:48,867 --> 02:04:52,036
- Is this some test?
- No, no tests.

1599
02:04:54,956 --> 02:04:56,539
You have your mother's hands.

1600
02:05:06,717 --> 02:05:08,886
You're an interesting species...

1601
02:05:09,554 --> 02:05:11,514
...an interesting mix.

1602
02:05:12,431 --> 02:05:15,225
You're capable of
such beautiful dreams...

1603
02:05:16,269 --> 02:05:18,729
...and such horrible nightmares.

1604
02:05:19,898 --> 02:05:21,731
You feel so lost...

1605
02:05:22,317 --> 02:05:25,277
...so cut off, so alone.

1606
02:05:26,738 --> 02:05:28,488
Only you're not.

1607
02:05:30,573 --> 02:05:32,115
See...

1608
02:05:32,576 --> 02:05:34,202
In all our searching...

1609
02:05:34,411 --> 02:05:37,913
...the only thing we've found
that makes the emptiness bearable...

1610
02:05:38,082 --> 02:05:39,707
...is each other.

1611
02:05:43,462 --> 02:05:45,380
What happens now?

1612
02:05:46,422 --> 02:05:47,923
Now?

1613
02:05:48,841 --> 02:05:50,635
You go home.

1614
02:05:50,802 --> 02:05:52,220
ELLIE:
Home?

1615
02:05:52,387 --> 02:05:55,472
But I have so many questions.

1616
02:05:55,640 --> 02:05:57,766
Do we get to come back?

1617
02:05:58,644 --> 02:06:00,895
This was just a first step.

1618
02:06:01,063 --> 02:06:02,814
In time, you'll take another.

1619
02:06:04,399 --> 02:06:06,775
But other people need to see
what I've seen...

1620
02:06:06,944 --> 02:06:09,988
This is the way it's been done
for billions of years.

1621
02:06:11,990 --> 02:06:14,617
- But I...
- Small moves, Ellie.

1622
02:06:16,078 --> 02:06:17,996
Small moves.

1623
02:07:01,079 --> 02:07:02,872
We've got video on Ellie.
Five-by-five.

1624
02:07:03,082 --> 02:07:04,957
STEVE:
She's through! She is in the net.

1625
02:07:05,126 --> 02:07:08,127
She's alive. Get the White House.
Get the president on the phone.

1626
02:07:08,296 --> 02:07:10,671
What's going on, Steve? How is she?
How is she?

1627
02:07:10,840 --> 02:07:12,548
STEVE:
Ellie, this is Control. Do you copy?

1628
02:07:12,716 --> 02:07:14,760
KENT: What's going on?
- I don't know. Hang on.

1629
02:07:14,926 --> 02:07:16,552
- She is alive.
STEVE: Put her on the PA.

1630
02:07:16,720 --> 02:07:18,305
Ellie, just hold on tight.

1631
02:07:18,930 --> 02:07:22,225
We're still trying to determine
the nature of the malfunction...

1632
02:07:22,393 --> 02:07:24,895
...but the important thing is you're okay.

1633
02:07:25,063 --> 02:07:26,229
What?

1634
02:07:26,396 --> 02:07:30,192
It's all right, Ellie.
The important thing is that you're safe.

1635
02:07:31,152 --> 02:07:33,444
What malfunction?

1636
02:07:34,780 --> 02:07:36,238
What...?

1637
02:07:37,408 --> 02:07:39,033
What happened?

1638
02:07:40,369 --> 02:07:42,037
What day is this?

1639
02:07:42,704 --> 02:07:45,707
I'm sorry, Ellie,
did you say what day?

1640
02:07:46,792 --> 02:07:49,043
How long was I gone?

1641
02:07:50,796 --> 02:07:55,591
Ellie, the IPV dropped
straight through the Machine.

1642
02:07:55,760 --> 02:07:57,426
You didn't go anywhere.

1643
02:07:58,304 --> 02:08:01,640
But I did. I did go.

1644
02:08:01,807 --> 02:08:04,184
That's what I've been trying
to tell everyone.

1645
02:08:08,648 --> 02:08:11,733
But the headset
didn't record a single image?

1646
02:08:11,900 --> 02:08:14,528
Just this. Static.

1647
02:08:14,737 --> 02:08:15,779
Thank you.

1648
02:08:15,947 --> 02:08:19,364
Now, doctor, let me show you
what we saw.

1649
02:08:28,833 --> 02:08:32,670
Forty-three separate remote cameras
show exactly the same event.

1650
02:08:32,837 --> 02:08:34,380
The IPV dropped straight through.

1651
02:08:34,547 --> 02:08:38,134
Everyone who watched
saw exactly the same thing.

1652
02:08:38,301 --> 02:08:40,136
Nothing happened.

1653
02:08:41,470 --> 02:08:43,764
How do you explain this, doctor?

1654
02:08:45,766 --> 02:08:46,891
I can't.

1655
02:08:47,101 --> 02:08:48,560
CLINTON:
I would encourage you...

1656
02:08:50,354 --> 02:08:54,524
...not to inflame this situation
beyond the facts.

1657
02:08:54,693 --> 02:08:58,112
Let us deal with this on the facts.

1658
02:08:58,279 --> 02:09:01,157
We are monitoring
what has actually happened.

1659
02:09:01,323 --> 02:09:06,662
We are taking what we believe
is factually appropriate steps.

1660
02:09:06,829 --> 02:09:10,039
Amid a flurry of accusations
and counter-accusations...

1661
02:09:10,250 --> 02:09:12,835
...by the nations representing
the Machine Consortium...

1662
02:09:13,002 --> 02:09:15,921
...the president has ordered
a special inquiry.

1663
02:09:16,131 --> 02:09:18,923
However, the appointment
to the committee of Michael Kitz...

1664
02:09:19,134 --> 02:09:21,969
...who has recently resigned
as National Security Advisor...

1665
02:09:22,136 --> 02:09:24,471
...has raised a number of eyebrows
on Capitol Hill.

1666
02:09:24,639 --> 02:09:28,434
I have made no decision to run for
Congress, I have announced no candidacy.

1667
02:09:28,601 --> 02:09:31,186
The fact that I resigned
as National Security Advisor...

1668
02:09:31,354 --> 02:09:33,063
...has nothing to do with anything...

1669
02:09:33,230 --> 02:09:36,399
...other than I want to devote
all of my energy to this inquiry.

1670
02:09:37,152 --> 02:09:41,820
The people of the world have a right
to know what really happened.

1671
02:09:42,655 --> 02:09:45,158
And yet every scientific
instrument confirms...

1672
02:09:45,326 --> 02:09:49,496
...the IPV was out of contact
for only a fraction of a second.

1673
02:09:49,662 --> 02:09:51,706
Isn't that correct, doctor?

1674
02:09:53,417 --> 02:09:55,710
A fraction of a second Earth time, yes.

1675
02:09:56,587 --> 02:09:57,837
SENATOR:
Earth time?

1676
02:09:58,005 --> 02:10:01,632
ELLIE: Senator, I believe that the Machine
opened up a wormhole...

1677
02:10:01,801 --> 02:10:06,762
...a tunnel through the fabric of space-time,
also known as an Einstein-Rosen Bridge.

1678
02:10:06,930 --> 02:10:11,059
Now, because of the effects of general
relativity, what I experienced as 18 hours...

1679
02:10:11,226 --> 02:10:13,478
...passed instantaneously on Earth.

1680
02:10:13,645 --> 02:10:17,981
Isn't it true that these wormholes you
speak of are merely theoretical predictions?

1681
02:10:18,149 --> 02:10:20,902
There is no evidence
they actually exist, is there?

1682
02:10:21,069 --> 02:10:22,779
ELLIE:
There is no direct evidence, no.

1683
02:10:22,947 --> 02:10:24,697
KITZ:
Tell me something, doctor...

1684
02:10:24,864 --> 02:10:27,992
...why do you think these aliens
would go to all this trouble?

1685
02:10:28,159 --> 02:10:32,372
Bring you tens of thousands of light years
and then send you home without proof?

1686
02:10:33,039 --> 02:10:35,750
They said that's how it's been done
for billions of years.

1687
02:10:36,126 --> 02:10:39,712
KITZ: That's very neat. You have no proof
because they didn't want you to have any.

1688
02:10:39,880 --> 02:10:44,634
A phenomenon known in psychiatric circles,
I believe, as a self-reinforcing delusion.

1689
02:10:45,219 --> 02:10:46,845
Is that what you think? Delusional?

1690
02:10:47,011 --> 02:10:51,140
KITZ: Well, I do think you may have suffered
some kind of an episode. Yeah, I do.

1691
02:10:51,307 --> 02:10:54,185
Doctor, I'd like to propose
an alternate hypothesis...

1692
02:10:54,395 --> 02:10:58,064
...and I'd like you to bring
your scientific expertise to bear on it.

1693
02:10:58,231 --> 02:11:01,442
To fake a signal from Vega...

1694
02:11:02,110 --> 02:11:03,694
...what would you need?

1695
02:11:05,404 --> 02:11:09,198
You would need a satellite to transmit
the signal, but it would be impossible to...

1696
02:11:09,367 --> 02:11:13,287
You'd need a satellite and need launch
capabilities to put the satellite into orbit.

1697
02:11:13,453 --> 02:11:16,664
And the message itself.
To put something like this together...

1698
02:11:16,832 --> 02:11:19,126
...so complex,
drawing on many disciplines...

1699
02:11:19,293 --> 02:11:21,252
- Would be impossible.
KITZ: Impossible?

1700
02:11:22,546 --> 02:11:24,463
Impossible?

1701
02:11:24,631 --> 02:11:28,260
Is there anyone who might
have been up to the challenge?

1702
02:11:28,427 --> 02:11:30,887
Someone with extraordinary
technical expertise...

1703
02:11:31,055 --> 02:11:33,265
...enormous financial resources...

1704
02:11:33,432 --> 02:11:37,810
...someone perverse enough,
eccentric enough to come up with the idea?

1705
02:11:39,188 --> 02:11:40,229
Hadden?

1706
02:11:41,189 --> 02:11:43,649
S. R. Hadden.

1707
02:11:43,818 --> 02:11:46,444
[CROWD MURMURING]

1708
02:11:47,947 --> 02:11:50,990
You're implying that this was
all some kind of a hoax?

1709
02:11:51,158 --> 02:11:52,408
That he engineered this?

1710
02:11:52,577 --> 02:11:53,827
KITZ:
S. R. Hadden...

1711
02:11:53,994 --> 02:11:58,873
...a legendary power broker and manipulator
in perhaps his final bid for immortality.

1712
02:11:59,042 --> 02:12:01,710
Maybe he wanted to explore
and exploit new technologies...

1713
02:12:01,877 --> 02:12:04,087
...and get the governments
to pick up the tab.

1714
02:12:04,296 --> 02:12:07,048
Perhaps this was his
final altruistic gesture...

1715
02:12:07,300 --> 02:12:11,011
...to unite the world in some common goal.
Maybe all of the above.

1716
02:12:11,179 --> 02:12:16,099
S. R. Hadden, a brilliant
and complicated man.

1717
02:12:18,645 --> 02:12:22,898
Doctor, are you familiar
with the scientific precept...

1718
02:12:23,065 --> 02:12:25,192
...known as Occam's razor?

1719
02:12:31,405 --> 02:12:32,573
ELLIE:
Yes.

1720
02:12:34,576 --> 02:12:36,661
It means that all things being equal...

1721
02:12:36,828 --> 02:12:39,329
...the simplest explanation
tends to be the right one.

1722
02:12:39,497 --> 02:12:41,039
KITZ:
Exactly.

1723
02:12:41,207 --> 02:12:43,667
Now, you tell me.
What is more likely here?

1724
02:12:43,835 --> 02:12:47,296
That a message from aliens
results in a magical machine...

1725
02:12:47,463 --> 02:12:50,173
...that whisks you away
to the center of the galaxy...

1726
02:12:50,384 --> 02:12:53,260
...to go windsurfing with your dad
and a split second later...

1727
02:12:53,427 --> 02:12:56,889
...returns you home
without a single shred of proof?

1728
02:12:57,056 --> 02:13:00,850
Or that your experience
is the result of being...

1729
02:13:01,019 --> 02:13:05,480
...the unwitting star in the farewell
performance of one S.R. Hadden?

1730
02:13:05,649 --> 02:13:09,443
A man with the means, motive and
opportunity to play you and the rest of us...

1731
02:13:09,694 --> 02:13:13,905
...as pawns in the biggest, most elaborate,
most expensive hoax of all time?

1732
02:13:15,199 --> 02:13:17,118
MAN:
Dr. Arroway.

1733
02:13:18,996 --> 02:13:23,373
You come to us with no evidence,
no record...

1734
02:13:23,542 --> 02:13:25,333
...no artifacts.

1735
02:13:25,502 --> 02:13:29,671
Only a story that, to put it mildly,
strains credibility.

1736
02:13:30,798 --> 02:13:33,926
Over half a trillion dollars were spent.

1737
02:13:34,094 --> 02:13:37,095
Dozens of lives were lost.

1738
02:13:37,722 --> 02:13:42,435
Are you really gonna sit there
and tell us we should just take this all...

1739
02:13:43,185 --> 02:13:44,729
...on faith?

1740
02:13:48,734 --> 02:13:50,943
KITZ:
Please answer the question, doctor.

1741
02:13:54,863 --> 02:13:56,948
Is it possible that it didn't happen?

1742
02:13:57,115 --> 02:13:58,283
Yes.

1743
02:13:58,451 --> 02:14:00,993
[CROWD MURMURING]

1744
02:14:01,162 --> 02:14:04,288
As a scientist I must concede that.
I must volunteer that.

1745
02:14:08,627 --> 02:14:10,545
KITZ:
Wait a minute, let me get this straight.

1746
02:14:10,712 --> 02:14:14,591
You admit you have absolutely no
physical evidence to back up your story?

1747
02:14:14,925 --> 02:14:15,966
Yes.

1748
02:14:16,135 --> 02:14:19,179
You admit that you very well may have
hallucinated this whole thing?

1749
02:14:19,345 --> 02:14:22,140
- Yes.
- You admit that if you were in our position...

1750
02:14:22,307 --> 02:14:26,060
...you would respond with exactly the same
degree of incredulity and skepticism?

1751
02:14:26,228 --> 02:14:27,479
Yes.

1752
02:14:27,645 --> 02:14:30,606
Then why don't you simply withdraw
your testimony and concede...

1753
02:14:30,774 --> 02:14:35,944
...that this journey to the center of
the galaxy in fact never took place?

1754
02:14:38,948 --> 02:14:40,949
Because I can't.

1755
02:14:41,118 --> 02:14:43,828
[CROWD MURMURING]

1756
02:14:47,500 --> 02:14:51,168
I had an experience.

1757
02:14:52,837 --> 02:14:55,422
I can't prove it. I can't even explain it.

1758
02:14:55,591 --> 02:14:58,676
But everything that I know as
a human being, everything I am...

1759
02:14:58,844 --> 02:15:00,970
...tells me it was real.

1760
02:15:03,015 --> 02:15:06,893
I was given something wonderful,
something that changed me forever.

1761
02:15:07,060 --> 02:15:08,603
A vision...

1762
02:15:08,770 --> 02:15:10,854
...of the universe...

1763
02:15:11,023 --> 02:15:13,690
...that tells us undeniably...

1764
02:15:13,859 --> 02:15:16,109
...how tiny and insignificant...

1765
02:15:16,277 --> 02:15:19,988
...and how rare and precious we all are.

1766
02:15:21,157 --> 02:15:23,574
A vision that tells us
that we belong to something...

1767
02:15:23,743 --> 02:15:29,413
...that is greater than ourselves,
that we are not... That none of us are alone.

1768
02:15:34,045 --> 02:15:38,047
I wish I could share that.

1769
02:15:40,551 --> 02:15:41,717
I wish...

1770
02:15:43,179 --> 02:15:47,224
...that everyone,
if even for one moment...

1771
02:15:47,391 --> 02:15:53,146
...could feel that awe
and humility and hope.

1772
02:15:53,564 --> 02:15:55,565
But...

1773
02:16:01,738 --> 02:16:04,032
That continues to be my wish.

1774
02:16:45,199 --> 02:16:48,533
MAN 1: Dr. Arroway, get a picture, please?
Get a photo over here?

1775
02:16:50,162 --> 02:16:51,787
WOMAN:
Here comes Ellie.

1776
02:17:28,075 --> 02:17:30,993
MAN 2:
Reverend Joss! Reverend Joss!

1777
02:17:31,161 --> 02:17:34,538
MAN 3: Reverend Joss, what do you
believe? What do you believe?

1778
02:17:38,793 --> 02:17:42,797
As a person of faith, I'm bound by
a different covenant than Dr. Arroway.

1779
02:17:44,549 --> 02:17:46,800
But our goal is one and the same.

1780
02:17:47,301 --> 02:17:48,927
The pursuit of truth.

1781
02:17:52,474 --> 02:17:53,765
I, for one, believe her.

1782
02:18:17,331 --> 02:18:20,208
So, what happens now?
We give her a medal?

1783
02:18:20,376 --> 02:18:23,253
I'd say at least a healthy grant.

1784
02:18:23,421 --> 02:18:26,880
I assume you read the confidential report
from the investigating committee?

1785
02:18:27,091 --> 02:18:28,842
KITZ:
I flipped through it.

1786
02:18:29,010 --> 02:18:33,220
I was especially interested
in the section on Arroway's video unit.

1787
02:18:34,014 --> 02:18:36,349
The one that recorded the static.

1788
02:18:37,601 --> 02:18:39,310
Continue.

1789
02:18:39,936 --> 02:18:43,772
The fact that it recorded static
isn't what interests me.

1790
02:18:48,611 --> 02:18:49,987
Continue.

1791
02:18:50,864 --> 02:18:52,699
What interests me...

1792
02:18:52,867 --> 02:18:56,702
...is that it recorded
approximately 18 hours of it.

1793
02:19:01,959 --> 02:19:03,877
That is interesting, isn't it?

1794
02:19:10,550 --> 02:19:14,387
ELLIE: You can see over there,
we're building 45 brand-new dishes.

1795
02:19:14,555 --> 02:19:18,515
And that means when you put them
together with all the radio telescopes...

1796
02:19:18,683 --> 02:19:20,184
...all over the world...

1797
02:19:20,352 --> 02:19:25,022
...then we get to hear farther into space
than anybody has ever heard before.

1798
02:19:25,191 --> 02:19:26,230
Yeah.

1799
02:19:26,398 --> 02:19:29,234
Are there other people
out there in the universe?

1800
02:19:30,278 --> 02:19:33,030
That's a good question.
What do you think, huh?

1801
02:19:33,614 --> 02:19:36,950
- I don't know.
- That's a good answer.

1802
02:19:37,826 --> 02:19:38,869
Skeptic, huh?

1803
02:19:40,163 --> 02:19:45,041
The important thing is that you all
keep searching for your own answers.

1804
02:19:45,209 --> 02:19:48,045
I'll tell you one thing
about the universe, though.

1805
02:19:48,212 --> 02:19:52,091
The universe is a pretty big place.

1806
02:19:53,093 --> 02:19:58,596
It's bigger than anything
anyone has ever dreamed of before.

1807
02:20:00,183 --> 02:20:01,850
So if it's just us...

1808
02:20:03,477 --> 02:20:06,271
...it seems like an awful waste of space.

1809
02:20:07,773 --> 02:20:09,148
Right?
